": "low", "example_use_case": "A development finance institution overlays socioeconomic vulnerability indices with flood risk maps to assess the disproportionate risk to marginalised communities in Bihar for ESRS S3-3 affected community disclosure.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Harmonized World Soil Database", "category": "Land use, land cover & fragmentation", "sub_category": "soil type & condition", "short_description": "Soil type classification from the FAO Harmonized World Soil Database", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-E (Evaluate): soil quality as ecosystem condition indicator; Dependency disclosure (soil-based production)", "TNFD_metric_type": "ecosystem condition \u2013 soil", "TNFD_code": "C5.0", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Land; Steps: Assess; Pressure: soil degradation; metric: soil organic carbon, soil type", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E4-5 (soil ecosystem condition); ESRS E2-5 (soil contamination)", "India_relevance": "medium", "India_notes": "FAO HWSD v2 and SoilGrids freely available. India has NBSS&LUP (National Bureau of Soil Survey) soil maps at 1:250K. Relevance for agri-food sector and mining.", "Darukaa_status": "not_core", "input_data_required": "FAO HWSD, SoilGrids, NBSS&LUP soil maps", "open_data_sources": ["FAO HWSD v2", "ISRIC SoilGrids 250m", "NBSS&LUP India soil maps", "ICAR soil health data", "Copernicus Soil Moisture"], "access_type": "open", "computation_complexity": "low", "example_use_case": "An agri-food company assesses baseline soil type and condition across its sourcing region in Punjab for TNFD Evaluate soil dependency disclosure.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Distance to green areas", "category": "Nature-based solutions & green infrastructure", "sub_category": "urban green access", "short_description": "Distance from each point to the nearest urban green area", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-E (Evaluate): urban green area as NbS ecosystem service; Opportunity & Dependency", "TNFD_metric_type": "opportunities \u2013 urban