"A food company assesses nitrogen fertiliser pollution risk in its wheat sourcing watershed in Punjab using FAO and CPCB data to disclose water-quality impacts under ESRS E2-4 and TNFD Evaluate.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Toxic metals soil pollution", "category": "Air quality & pollution", "sub_category": "soil & land contamination", "short_description": "Soil contamination by toxic heavy metals", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-E (Evaluate): soil contamination as ecosystem condition stressor; Impact", "TNFD_metric_type": "impacts \u2013 soil pollution / toxic contamination", "TNFD_code": "C2.1 | C2.0", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Land; Steps: Assess; Pressure: pollution \u2013 toxic substances; metric: heavy metal concentration mg/kg", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E2-5 (soil contamination); ESRS E2-3 (material pollution policy)", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "Mining legacy pollution (arsenic in WB, lead in UP) and industrial sites are major issues. CPCB/SPCBs maintain contaminated sites register. NGT orders drive remediation disclosures.", "Darukaa_status": "not_core", "input_data_required": "in-situ soil sampling, CPCB contaminated sites register, geochemical maps", "open_data_sources": ["CPCB contaminated sites India", "GSI geochemical atlas India", "FOREGS geochemical baseline", "ISRIC SoilGrids toxic metals", "JECFA/FAO soil quality guidelines"], "access_type": "mixed", "computation_complexity": "medium", "example_use_case": "A mining company uses GSI geochemical maps and CPCB contaminated sites data to disclose soil heavy metal contamination around legacy mine sites under ESRS E2-5 soil contamination datapoint.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Land Cover Classification", "category": "Land use, land cover & fragmentation", "sub_category": "land cover classification", "short_description": "CLC-based land cover classification; prerequisite for biodiversity maps", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-L (Locate): baseline spatial context; LEAP-E (Evaluate): land-cover change as ecosystem condition proxy; Impact disclosure", "TNFD_metric_type": "ecosystem condition \u2013 land cover", "TNFD_code": "C1.0 | C1.1 | C5.0", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Land; Steps: Assess & Track; Pressure: land-use change; metric: % natural land cover", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E4-5 (ecosystem extent); ESRS E4-4 (targets on biodiversity); ESRS E2-5 (soil contamination)", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "India's national LULC maps available at 1:50K from ISRO/NRSC via Bhuvan portal. ESA WorldCover 10m and Dynamic World 10m usable for annual change detection. State Forest Reports (FSI) for forest class.", "Darukaa_status": "available", "input_data_required": "multispectral satellite imagery, ground reference data", "open_data_sources": ["ISRO LULC 1:50K (Bhuvan)", "ESA WorldCover 10m", "Google Dynamic World", "FSI India Forest Cover maps", "MODIS MCD12Q1"], "access_type": "open", "computation_complexity": "medium", "example_use_case": "A plantation company tracks annual changes in natural land cover across its concession in Madhya Pradesh using national LULC data to comply with ESRS E4-5 ecosystem extent disclosures.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Soil impermeability", "category": "Land use, land cover & fragmentation", "sub_category": "land artificialization", "short_description": "Degree of soil sealing / impervious surface coverage", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-L: locate where land has been sealed/built up; LEAP-E: assess ecosystem loss from impermeability; Impact & Dependency", "TNFD_metric_type": "ecosystem condition \u2013 land impermeability / seal", "TNFD_code": "C1.0 | C1.1 | C2.0", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Land; Steps: Assess, Act; Pressure: land-use change \u2013 urban expansion; metric: sealed surface %", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E4-5 (ecosystem extent \u2013 artificial surfaces); ESRS E3-3 (water targets, runoff); ESRS E2-5 (soil)", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "Urban sprawl fastest in Tier-2/3 Indian cities (Pune, Surat, Hyderabad). ISRO LULC and Copernicus GHSL provide built-up fraction. National Urban Digital Mission data complementary.", "Darukaa_status": "available", "input_data_required": "satellite LULC, built-up surface layer, DEM", "open_data_sources": ["GHSL Global Human Settlement Layer", "ISRO LULC Bhuvan", "ESA WorldCover", "Copernicus Urban Atlas", "Google Open Buildings India"], "access_type": "open", "computation_complexity": "low", "example_use_case": "A real estate developer in Bangalore quantifies the fraction of new built-up area replacing natural land over 5 years for TNFD Locate disclosures and ESRS E4-5 reporting.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Natural and Agricultural Areas", "category": "Land use, land cover & fragmentation", "sub_category": "land cover classification", "short_description": "Classification of land into natural vs agricultural area types", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-L (Locate): baseline spatial context; LEAP-E (Evaluate): land-cover change as ecosystem condition proxy; Impact disclosure", "TNFD_metric_type": "ecosystem condition \u2013 land cover", "TNFD_code": "C1.0 | C1.1", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Land; Steps: Assess & Track; Pressure: land-use change; metric: % natural land cover", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E4-5 (ecosystem extent); ESRS E4-4 (targets on biodiversity); ESRS E2-5 (soil contamination)", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "India's national LULC maps available at 1:50K from ISRO/NRSC via Bhuvan portal. ESA WorldCover 10m and Dynamic World 10m usable for annual change detection. State Forest Reports (FSI) for forest class.", "Darukaa_status": "available", "input_data_required": "multispectral satellite imagery, ground reference data", "open_data_sources": ["ISRO LULC 1:50K (Bhuvan)", "ESA WorldCover 10m", "Google Dynamic World", "FSI India Forest Cover maps", "MODIS MCD12Q1"], "access_type": "open", "computation_complexity": "medium", "example_use_case": "A plantation company tracks annual changes in natural land cover across its concession in Madhya Pradesh using national LULC data to comply with ESRS E4-5 ecosystem extent disclosures.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Spectrum device heatmap", "category": "Biodiversity & ecosystems", "sub_category": "in-situ biodiversity monitoring", "short_description": "Heatmap from in-field Spectrum IoT device sensor network", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-E (Evaluate): ground-truth ecosystem condition with real-time sensor data; Impact & Dependency monitoring", "TNFD_metric_type": "ecosystem condition \u2013 in-situ species activity", "TNFD_code": "C5.0", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Land; Steps: Track; Pressure: monitoring indicator for all pressures; metric: species activity index", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E4-5 (biodiversity monitoring method); ESRS E4-3 (action plans with KPIs)", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "Darukaa's bioacoustic and IoT sensor network is core differentiator in India. Deployable in agri-landscapes, forests, and wetlands. Relevant for BRSR Core ESG indicators on biodiversity.", "Darukaa_status": "available", "input_data_required": "IoT device telemetry, acoustic recordings, GPS coordinates", "open_data_sources": ["Darukaa Spectrum/proprietary", "iNaturalist India", "eBird India", "GBIF", "WII camera trap networks"], "access_type": "proprietary_client", "computation_complexity": "medium", "example_use_case": "A tea estate in Assam deploys Darukaa sensors to monitor pollinator activity and nocturnal biodiversity, providing ground-truth data for TNFD Evaluate disclosures and BRSR Core ESG reporting.", "additional_comments": null}, {"category": "Climate & physical risk", "sub_category": "extreme weather events", "short_description": "Historical spatial record of extreme weather events", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-A (Assess): acute physical climate risks from storms and extreme events; Risk disclosure", "TNFD_metric_type": "physical risk \u2013 extreme weather", "TNFD_code": "IFRS S2", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Atmosphere; Steps: Assess, Prioritise; Pressure: extreme weather; metric: event frequency and intensity trend", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E1-9 (physical risks \u2013 extreme precipitation, storms); ESRS E1-3 (scenario analysis)", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "India faces cyclones (Bay of Bengal), deluges, and hailstorms. IMD cyclone atlas, NDMA multi-hazard atlas, ISRO NRSC extreme event monitoring.", "Darukaa_status": "available", "input_data_required": "historical weather station data, IMD extreme event records, ERA5", "open_data_sources": ["IMD India extreme weather events", "NDMA multi-hazard atlas", "EM-DAT disaster database", "NOAA Storm Events DB", "ERA5 extreme indices"], "access_type": "open", "computation_complexity": "low", "example_use_case": "An insurer quantifies the frequency trend of extreme rainfall events at client sites in Maharashtra for TNFD physical risk scenario analysis and ESRS E1-9 disclosure.", "additional_comments": null, "original_name": "Extreme weather events"}, {"original_name": "Cultural and artistic heritage POIs", "category": "Socio-environmental & exposure", "sub_category": "cultural & heritage assets", "short_description": "Points of interest for cultural and artistic heritage sites", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-L (Locate): cultural heritage as context for nature-related risk / social licence; Impact", "TNFD_metric_type": "exposure index \u2013 cultural heritage", "TNFD_code": "No Annex 1/2 code \u2014 relates to TNFD Strategy D (priority locations) and stakeholder engagement guidance", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Land; Steps: Assess; Pressure: infrastructure, tourism pressure; metric: proximity/count", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS S3-3 (affected communities \u2013 indigenous/cultural sites); ESRS E4-2 (policy on sacred/cultural areas)", "India_relevance": "medium", "India_notes": "ASI (Archaeological Survey of India) maintains 3,691 centrally protected monuments. Forest Rights Act implications for indigenous communities near forested cultural sites.", "Darukaa_status": "not_core", "input_data_required": "ASI monument database, state heritage lists, NLCPR data", "open_data_sources": ["ASI India protected monuments list", "UNESCO World Heritage India", "OpenStreetMap heritage POIs", "Wikidata cultural heritage India", "State tourism department portals"], "access_type": "open", "computation_complexity": "low", "example_use_case": "An infrastructure developer screens its project corridor for proximity to ASI-protected monuments and forest communities under ESRS S3-3 affected community identification and India's LARR Act compliance.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Oasi Ecological Features Score", "category": "Nature-based solutions & green infrastructure", "sub_category": "managed nature restoration sites", "short_description": "Ecological features of our managed oasis sites", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-P (Prepare): track progress of NbS investments; Opportunity disclosure", "TNFD_metric_type": "opportunities \u2013 NbS / ecological restoration", "TNFD_code": "C1.1 | C5.0", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Land; Steps: Act, Track; Pressure: all; metric: restored area (ha), ecosystem health KPIs", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E4-3 (action plans \u2013 restoration); ESRS E4-4 (restoration targets and progress KPIs)", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "India's LCRMP and MoEFCC restoration targets under Bonn Challenge/UNCCD. Darukaa's oasis network is proprietary differentiator for real-time restoration monitoring.", "Darukaa_status": "available", "input_data_required": "Darukaa sensor network, satellite NDVI/habitat, bioacoustic data", "open_data_sources": ["Darukaa platform (proprietary)", "ISRO LULC restoration layers", "FSI India restoration data", "IUFRO restoration data", "GFW tree cover gain"], "access_type": "proprietary_client", "computation_complexity": "medium", "example_use_case": "A corporate's biodiversity offset project uses Darukaa's oasis data to track restoration progress with NDVI, bioacoustics, and pollinator KPIs for ESRS E4-4 restoration target reporting.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Aqueduct Water Risk", "category": "Water quantity & quality", "sub_category": "water stress & aridity", "short_description": "Water risk assessment using WRI Aqueduct data (baseline water stress, variability, etc.)", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-L (Locate): identify water-stressed locations; LEAP-E (Evaluate): assess water dependency risk; Dependency & Risk", "TNFD_metric_type": "dependencies \u2013 water stress / freshwater availability", "TNFD_code": "C3.0", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Freshwater; Steps: Assess, Interpret; Pressure: water withdrawal vs availability; metric: BWS (Baseline Water Stress)", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E3-1 (water stress areas policy); ESRS E3-4 (water targets in stressed areas); ESRS E3-3 (water withdrawal)", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "India has 18% of world population but 4% freshwater. WRI Aqueduct India data freely available. CWC water availability data at sub-basin level. High relevance for manufacturing, agri, textile sectors.", "Darukaa_status": "available", "input_data_required": "WRI Aqueduct data, CWC streamflow data, GRACE groundwater, LULC", "open_data_sources": ["WRI Aqueduct 4.0", "CWC India water data", "NASA GRACE groundwater anomaly", "IMD precipitation data", "FAO AQUASTAT India"], "access_type": "open", "computation_complexity": "low", "example_use_case": "A textile company in Tirupur uses WRI Aqueduct data to identify high water-stress sourcing locations and discloses under ESRS E3-1 water stress policy and TNFD Locate disclosures.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "IUCN Red List", "category": "Biodiversity & ecosystems", "sub_category": "threatened species", "short_description": "Evaluation of threatened species presence in the area against IUCN Red List categories", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-L (Locate): flag sites near threatened-species ranges; LEAP-E (Evaluate): quantify species at risk; Impact & Risk disclosure", "TNFD_metric_type": "ecosystem condition \u2013 threatened species", "TNFD_code": "C5.0", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Land/Freshwater/Ocean; Steps: Assess, Interpret; Pressure: all pressures; metric: number of IUCN threatened species present", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E4-5 (biodiversity state \u2013 IUCN Red List species); ESRS E4-1 (transition plan); IRO identification", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "IUCN Red List freely accessible; overlay with WII Protected Area Network, Wildlife Crime Control Bureau data. India hosts 172 IUCN CR/EN species. Schedule I of Wildlife Protection Act 1972 as Indian legal layer.", "Darukaa_status": "available", "input_data_required": "IUCN Red List species range maps, protected area boundaries, LULC", "open_data_sources": ["IUCN Red List API", "GBIF species occurrence", "WII Protected Area Network India", "Map of Life", "MoEFCC Species lists"], "access_type": "open", "computation_complexity": "low", "example_use_case": "A mining company in Odisha uses IUCN Red List layer to flag threatened species within 10 km of a proposed mine, fulfilling TNFD Locate step and ESRS E4 IRO identification requirements.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Biodiversity Report", "category": "Composite / platform scores", "sub_category": "integrated biodiversity report", "short_description": "Full biodiversity report with data aggregation, charts, and AI analysis", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-P (Prepare): supports integrated reporting and board-level disclosure; aggregates multiple LEAP outputs; Impact, Dependency, Risk & Opportunity", "TNFD_metric_type": "composite platform score / integrated report", "TNFD_code": "C5.0", "SBTN_link": "Realm: cross-realm; Steps: all; metric: composite index or AI narrative", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E4 (all datapoints via aggregation); ESRS 2-SBM-3 (sustainability due diligence); supports BRSR Core ESG disclosure", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "Composite outputs are 