 "sub_category": "pollination & ecosystem services", "short_description": "Potential of the landscape to provide nectar resources for pollinators", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-E: dependency on ecosystem services (pollination); LEAP-A: assess risk to service continuity; Dependencies & Opportunities", "TNFD_metric_type": "dependencies \u2013 pollination ecosystem service", "TNFD_code": "C5.0", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Land; Steps: Assess & Track; Pressure: habitat loss, pesticide use; metric: pollinator abundance index", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E4-5 (ecosystem services \u2013 pollination); ESRS E4-2 (policies on biodiversity); IRO dependency disclosure", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "India supports ~700 wild bee species; pollination dependency critical for >60% of food crops. ICAR data on crop-pollinator relationships available. ISRO landcover + floral phenology models applicable.", "Darukaa_status": "available", "input_data_required": "LULC map, floral resource layer, nesting substrate map, pesticide application data", "open_data_sources": ["ESA WorldCover", "ISRO Bhuvan LULC", "GBIF pollinator occurrences", "InVEST Pollination model", "ICAR crop-pollination studies"], "access_type": "mixed", "computation_complexity": "high", "example_use_case": "A food & beverage company maps pollinator abundance across its sourcing landscapes in Karnataka to quantify dependency and disclose under TNFD ecosystem service dependencies.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Flowering Area", "category": "Nature-based solutions & green infrastructure", "sub_category": "floral & green resource provision", "short_description": "Area and density of flowering plant cover supporting pollinators", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-E (Evaluate): floral resource as supporting ecosystem service for pollinators; Dependency & Opportunity", "TNFD_metric_type": "dependencies \u2013 floral resource provisioning", "TNFD_code": "C5.0", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Land; Steps: Assess, Track; Pressure: habitat loss, land use; metric: flowering area %, nectar resource index", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E4-5 (ecosystem services \u2013 pollination); ESRS E4-3 (action plans including habitat enhancement)", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "India has 17,000+ flowering plant species. ISRO LULC combined with phenological satellite data (Sentinel-2 Red Edge) enables flowering area mapping. Relevant for honey, horticulture, seed industries.", "Darukaa_status": "available", "input_data_required": "Sentinel-2 vegetation indices, floral diversity field data, LULC", "open_data_sources": ["Sentinel-2 MSI (Copernicus)", "ISRO Bhuvan LULC", "GBIF plant occurrence India", "BSI (Botanical Survey of India)", "iNaturalist India"], "access_type": "mixed", "computation_complexity": "medium", "example_use_case": "A honey producer in Himachal Pradesh maps flowering area and nectariferous potential across the landscape to disclose pollination ecosystem service dependency under TNFD Evaluate and ESRS E4-5.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Climate Change (risk)", "category": "Climate & physical risk", "sub_category": "climate change exposure", "short_description": "Change in average temperature vs 1950\u20131970 baseline and increased extreme event frequency", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-A (Assess): long-term physical risk from climate change; LEAP-P (Prepare): transition risk; Risk & Opportunity", "TNFD_metric_type": "physical risk \u2013 chronic temperature increase", "TNFD_code": "C5.0", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Atmosphere; Steps: Assess, Prioritise; Pressure: climate change; metric: temperature anomaly vs baseline", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E1-9 (physical risk \u2013 chronic temperature rise); ESRS E1-3 (scenario analysis)", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "India has warmed ~0.7\u00b0C since 1901 (IMD); projected +2\u20134\u00b0C by 2100 under high emission scenarios. IITM CCCR 2020 India's first comprehensive climate change report is key reference.", "Darukaa_status": "available", "input_data_required": "historical temperature records, CMIP6 projections, ERA5", "open_data_sources": ["IITM CCCR 2020 India CC report", "IMD historical data", "ERA5 (Copernicus)", "CMIP6 ESGF portal", "NASA NEX-GDDP-CMIP6"], "access_type": "open", "computation_complexity": "medium", "example_use_case": "A financial institution stress-tests its project finance portfolio against the IITM 2\u00b0C and 4\u00b0C scenarios to quantify transition and physical climate risk for TNFD Assess disclosures.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Wind (risk)", "category": "Climate & physical risk", "sub_category": "wind risk", "short_description": "Wind speed and direction analysis over time", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-A (Assess): physical risk from wind; LEAP-P (Prepare): structural resilience planning; Risk disclosure", "TNFD_metric_type": "physical risk \u2013 wind", "TNFD_code": "C5.0", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Atmosphere; Steps: Assess; Pressure: wind stress; metric: max wind speed return period", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E1-9 (physical risks \u2013 wind storms)", "India_relevance": "medium", "India_notes": "Cyclone-prone Indian coasts: Tamil Nadu, Odisha, West Bengal, Gujarat. IMD cyclone atlases and NDMA wind hazard maps available.", "Darukaa_status": "available", "input_data_required": "wind speed reanalysis (ERA5), cyclone track data, IMD station records", "open_data_sources": ["ERA5 wind speed (Copernicus CDS)", "IMD cyclone track data", "NDMA wind hazard maps", "Open-Meteo API", "CMIP6 wind projections"], "access_type": "open", "computation_complexity": "low", "example_use_case": "A renewable energy developer assesses mean and extreme wind conditions at a proposed offshore wind site using ERA5 reanalysis for ESRS E1-9 physical risk disclosure.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Heat Wave", "category": "Climate & physical risk", "sub_category": "heat risk", "short_description": "Extended periods of extreme temperatures causing infrastructure strain and productivity loss", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-A (Assess): acute and chronic physical risk from heat; LEAP-P (Prepare): resilience planning; Risk disclosure", "TNFD_metric_type": "physical risk \u2013 heat stress / extreme heat", "TNFD_code": "IFRS S2", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Atmosphere/Land; Steps: Assess, Prioritise; Pressure: climate change \u2013 temperature; metric: heat stress days, WBGT", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E1-9 (physical risks \u2013 chronic heat, extreme heat events); ESRS E1-4 (transition activities in heat-vulnerable sectors)", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "India's NDMA National Heat Action Plans cover 23 states. Wet Bulb Globe Temperature (WBGT) increasingly used. IMD provides heat wave alerts. Labour productivity losses due to heat are BRSR-material.", "Darukaa_status": "available", "input_data_required": "temperature/humidity time series, WBGT model, heat wave indices", "open_data_sources": ["IMD heat wave data India", "ERA5-Land", "Copernicus C3S climate indicators", "NCEI NOAA heat indices", "Open-Meteo API"], "access_type": "open", "computation_complexity": "low", "example_use_case": "A garment manufacturer in Tamil Nadu discloses worker exposure to heat stress days above WBGT threshold using local IMD data, reporting under ESRS E1-9 and BRSR occupational health indicators.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Cold Wave", "category": "Climate & physical risk", "sub_category": "cold risk", "short_description": "Extended periods of extremely low temperatures impacting infrastructure and operations", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-A (Assess): acute physical risk from cold waves; Risk disclosure", "TNFD_metric_type": "physical risk \u2013 cold wave", "TNFD_code": "IFRS S2", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Atmosphere; Steps: Assess; Pressure: climate extremes \u2013 cold; metric: cold wave frequency", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E1-9 (physical risks \u2013 cold extremes)", "India_relevance": "medium", "India_notes": "Relevant for North India (Delhi, Punjab, UP, Himachal Pradesh) and Himalayan regions. IMD cold wave bulletins as primary data source.", "Darukaa_status": "available", "input_data_required": "IMD cold wave data, ERA5 temperature, crop cold-stress models", "open_data_sources": ["IMD India cold wave bulletins", "ERA5-Land temperature", "Open-Meteo API", "NASA POWER", "NOAA GHCN India stations"], "access_type": "open", "computation_complexity": "low", "example_use_case": "A horticulture company in Himachal Pradesh discloses cold wave risk to orchard productivity using IMD historical cold wave data for ESRS E1-9 chronic physical risk assessment.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Total Precipitation", "category": "Climate & physical risk", "sub_category": "precipitation pattern", "short_description": "Total precipitation (rain + snow) analysis over time", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-A (Assess): chronic and acute physical risk from changing precipitation; Risk & Dependency disclosure", "TNFD_metric_type": "physical risk \u2013 precipitation change", "TNFD_code": "C3.0", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Freshwater/Atmosphere; Steps: Assess; Pressure: altered precipitation; metric: precipitation trend, anomaly index", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E1-9 (physical risks \u2013 precipitation); ESRS E3-4 (water targets linked to rainfall)", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "India's southwest monsoon accounts for 70\u201390% of annual rainfall. IMD monsoon data essential. CMIP6 projections show increased monsoon variability. High relevance for agriculture, water utilities.", "Darukaa_status": "available", "input_data_required": "IMD gridded rainfall, TRMM/GPM satellite precipitation, ERA5", "open_data_sources": ["IMD India gridded rainfall 0.25\u00b0", "NASA GPM IMERG", "ERA5-Land precipitation", "CHIRPS precipitation", "TRMM 3B42"], "access_type": "open", "computation_complexity": "low", "example_use_case": "A water utility in Rajasthan uses IMD historical and projected rainfall trend data to disclose water availabi