rial.", "Darukaa_status": "available", "input_data_required": "temperature/humidity time series, WBGT model, heat wave indices", "open_data_sources": ["IMD heat wave data India", "ERA5-Land", "Copernicus C3S climate indicators", "NCEI NOAA heat indices", "Open-Meteo API"], "access_type": "open", "computation_complexity": "low", "example_use_case": "A garment manufacturer in Tamil Nadu discloses worker exposure to heat stress days above WBGT threshold using local IMD data, reporting under ESRS E1-9 and BRSR occupational health indicators.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Extreme Heat", "category": "Climate & physical risk", "sub_category": "heat risk", "short_description": "Record-breaking temperatures causing infrastructure failures and health risks", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-A (Assess): acute and chronic physical risk from heat; LEAP-P (Prepare): resilience planning; Risk disclosure", "TNFD_metric_type": "physical risk \u2013 heat stress / extreme heat", "TNFD_code": "IFRS S2", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Atmosphere/Land; Steps: Assess, Prioritise; Pressure: climate change \u2013 temperature; metric: heat stress days, WBGT", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E1-9 (physical risks \u2013 chronic heat, extreme heat events); ESRS E1-4 (transition activities in heat-vulnerable sectors)", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "India's NDMA National Heat Action Plans cover 23 states. Wet Bulb Globe Temperature (WBGT) increasingly used. IMD provides heat wave alerts. Labour productivity losses due to heat are BRSR-material.", "Darukaa_status": "available", "input_data_required": "temperature/humidity time series, WBGT model, heat wave indices", "open_data_sources": ["IMD heat wave data India", "ERA5-Land", "Copernicus C3S climate indicators", "NCEI NOAA heat indices", "Open-Meteo API"], "access_type": "open", "computation_complexity": "low", "example_use_case": "A garment manufacturer in Tamil Nadu discloses worker exposure to heat stress days above WBGT threshold using local IMD data, reporting under ESRS E1-9 and BRSR occupational health indicators.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Extreme Storm", "category": "Climate & physical risk", "sub_category": "extreme weather events", "short_description": "Violent storms with hurricane-force winds and risk of structural failure", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-A (Assess): acute physical climate risks from storms and extreme events; Risk disclosure", "TNFD_metric_type": "physical risk \u2013 extreme weather", "TNFD_code": "IFRS S2", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Atmosphere; Steps: Assess, Prioritise; Pressure: extreme weather; metric: event frequency and intensity trend", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E1-9 (physical risks \u2013 extreme precipitation, storms); ESRS E1-3 (scenario analysis)", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "India faces cyclones (Bay of Bengal), deluges, and hailstorms. IMD cyclone atlas, NDMA multi-hazard atlas, ISRO NRSC extreme event monitoring.", "Darukaa_status": "available", "input_data_required": "historical weather station data, IMD extreme event records, ERA5", "open_data_sources": ["IMD India extreme weather events", "NDMA multi-hazard atlas", "EM-DAT disaster database", "NOAA Storm Events DB", "ERA5 extreme indices"], "access_type": "open", "computation_complexity": "low", "example_use_case": "An insurer quantifies the frequency trend of extreme rainfall events at client sites in Maharashtra for TNFD physical risk scenario analysis and ESRS E1-9 disclosure.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Drought", "category": "Water quantity & quality", "sub_category": "water stress & aridity", "short_description": "Prolonged water scarcity with operational restrictions and increased costs", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-L (Locate): identify water-stressed locations; LEAP-E (Evaluate): assess water dependency risk; Dependency & Risk", "TNFD_metric_type": "dependencies \u2013 water stress / freshwater availability", "TNFD_code": "C3.0", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Freshwater; Steps: Assess, Interpret; Pressure: water withdrawal vs availability; metric: BWS (Baseline Water Stress)", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E3-1 (water stress areas policy); ESRS E3-4 (water targets in stressed areas); ESRS E3-3 (water withdrawal)", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "India has 18% of world population but 4% freshwater. WRI Aqueduct India data freely available. CWC water availability data at sub-basin level. High relevance for manufacturing, agri, textile sectors.", "Darukaa_status": "available", "input_data_required": "WRI Aqueduct data, CWC streamflow data, GRACE groundwater, LULC", "open_data_sources": ["WRI Aqueduct 4.0", "CWC India water data", "NASA GRACE groundwater anomaly", "IMD precipitation data", "FAO AQUASTAT India"], "access_type": "open", "computation_complexity": "low", "example_use_case": "A textile company in Tirupur uses WRI Aqueduct data to identify high water-stress sourcing locations and discloses under ESRS E3-1 water stress policy and TNFD Locate disclosures.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Desertification", "category": "Land use, land cover & fragmentation", "sub_category": "land degradation & desertification", "short_description": "Progressive land degradation with loss of productivity and land value", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-E (Evaluate): assess degraded and desertified land as ecosystem condition loss; LEAP-A: quantify impact on livelihoods; Impact & Risk", "TNFD_metric_type": "ecosystem condition \u2013 land degradation", "TNFD_code": "C2.0", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Land; Steps: Assess, Act; Pressure: land degradation; metric: LDN (Land Degradation Neutrality) indicator", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E4-5 (ecosystem condition \u2013 land degradation); ESRS E4-2 (policies on degraded land); linked to SDG 15.3", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "India has ~30% of land classified as degraded (ISRO/NRSC Desertification Atlas 2021). High relevance for Rajasthan, Jharkhand, Odisha. NRSC Desertification Atlas and SAC LDN indicators are primary sources.", "Darukaa_status": "planned", "input_data_required": "NDVI trend, soil erosion model, land productivity, SOC data", "open_data_sources": ["ISRO/NRSC Desertification Atlas India 2021", "FAO GloSOIL", "ESA WorldCover", "MODIS NDVI trend", "UNCCD LDN indicator data"], "access_type": "mixed", "computation_complexity": "medium", "example_use_case": "A cement company in Rajasthan maps desertification trends around its quarrying operations to disclose land degradation impacts under ESRS E4-5 and demonstrate LDN commitment.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Flood (risk)", "category": "Climate & physical risk", "sub_category": "flood & hydrogeological risk", "short_description": "Risk of flooding with structural damage and operational disruption", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-A (Assess): acute physical flood risk at site; LEAP-P (Prepare): risk management; Risk disclosure", "TNFD_metric_type": "physical risk \u2013 flood", "TNFD_code": "C5.0", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Freshwater/Land; Steps: Assess, Prioritise; Pressure: flood, precipitation change; metric: flood return period, assets at risk", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E1-9 (flood physical risk); ESRS E3-4 (water-related disaster risk)", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "India's CWC (Central Water Commission) maintains flood hazard maps for 150+ river basins. NDMA flood risk atlas, ISRO NRSC flood mapping products. High relevance for Bihar, Assam, Maharashtra coasts.", "Darukaa_status": "available", "input_data_required": "DEM, river network, rainfall data, flood hazard maps, land use", "open_data_sources": ["CWC India flood hazard maps", "NDMA flood risk atlas", "JRC Global Flood Database", "Copernicus EMS", "ISRO NRSC flood monitoring"], "access_type": "mixed", "computation_complexity": "medium", "example_use_case": "A logistics company assesses flood risk to its warehouses across the Brahmaputra floodplain using CWC flood maps and discloses exposure under ESRS E1-9 acute physical risk metrics.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Aridity (risk)", "category": "Water quantity & quality", "sub_category": "water stress & aridity", "short_description": "Long-term drying trend impacting land productivity and increasing water costs", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-L (Locate): identify water-stressed locations; LEAP-E (Evaluate): assess water dependency risk; Dependency & Risk", "TNFD_metric_type": "dependencies \u2013 water stress / freshwater availability", "TNFD_code": "C3.0", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Freshwater; Steps: Assess, Interpret; Pressure: water withdrawal vs availability; metric: BWS (Baseline Water Stress)", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E3-1 (water stress areas policy); ESRS E3-4 (water targets in stressed areas); ESRS E3-3 (water withdrawal)", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "India has 18% of world population but 4% freshwater. WRI Aqueduct India data freely available. CWC water availability data at sub-basin level. High relevance for manufacturing, agri, textile sectors.", "Darukaa_status": "available", "input_data_required": "WRI Aqueduct data, CWC streamflow data, GRACE groundwater, LULC", "open_data_sources": ["WRI Aqueduct 4.0", "CWC India water data", "NASA GRACE groundwater anomaly", "IMD precipitation data", "FAO AQUASTAT India"], "access_type": "open", "computation_complexity": "low", "example_use_case": "A textile company in Tirupur uses WRI Aqueduct data to identify high water-stress sourcing locations and discloses under ESRS E3-1 water stress policy and TNFD Locate disclosures.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Water Stress", "category": "Water quantity & quality", "sub_category": "water stress & aridity", "short_description": "Imbalance between water demand and supply leading to restrictions and rationing", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-L (Locate): identify water-stressed locations; LEAP-E (Evaluate): assess water dependency risk; Dependency & Risk", "TNFD_metric_type": "dependencies \u2013 water stress / freshwater availability", "TNFD_code": "C3.0 | C2.1", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Freshwater; Steps: Assess, Interpret; Pressure: water withdrawal vs availability; metric: BWS (Baseline Water Stress)", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E3-1 (water stress areas policy); ESRS E3-4 (water targets in stressed areas); ESRS E3-3 (water withdrawal)", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "India has 18% of world population but 4% freshwater. WRI Aqueduct India data freely available. CWC water availability data at sub-basin level. High relevance for manufacturing, agri, textile sectors.", "Darukaa_status": "available", "input_data_required": "WRI Aqueduct data, CWC streamflow data, GRACE groundwater, LULC", "open_data_sources": ["WRI Aqueduct 4.0", "CWC India water data", "NASA GRACE groundwater anomaly", "IMD precipitation data", "FAO AQUASTAT India"], "access_type": "open", "computation_complexity": "low", "example_use_case": "A textile company in Tirupur uses WRI Aqueduct data to identify high water-stress sourcing locations and discloses under ESRS E3-1 water stress policy and TNFD Locate disclosures.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Air Quality (risk)", "category": "Air quality & pollution", "sub_category": "air quality index", "short_description": "Health risk from air pollution and associated mortality rates", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-A (Assess): composite air quality health risk; Risk & Impact", "TNFD_metric_type": "impacts \u2013 air quality composite index", "TNFD_code": "C2.4", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Atmosphere; Steps: Assess; Pressure: air pollution; metric: AQI score", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E2-4 (air pollutants); ESRS S1-9 (worker/community health \u2013 air quality)", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "CPCB AQI system (India-specific 6 pollutant composite, scale 0\u2013500) is the standard. India AQI differs from US/EU systems. SAFAR provides city-specific AQI. National Clean Air Programme (NCAP) targets 40% PM reduction by 2026.", "Darukaa_status": "prototype", "input_data_required": "CPCB CAAQM AQI, PM2.5, PM10, NO2, SO2, O3, CO data", "open_data_sources": ["CPCB AQI India (real-time)", "SAFAR India AQI", "OpenAQ India", "IQAir India data", "WAQI World Air Quality Index"], "access_type": "mixed", "computation_complexity": "low", "example_use_case": "A real-estate developer uses India AQI data to disclose environmental quality around residential projects in Delhi-NCR for ESRS E2-4 community exposure indicators and BRSR ESG reporting.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Landslide (risk)", "category": "Climate & physical risk", "sub_category": "geophysical & mass movement risk", "short_description": "Risk of slope instability with potential damage to foundations and structures", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-A (Assess): geophysical risk at site; Risk disclosure", "TNFD_metric_type": "physical risk \u2013 seismic / landslide / volcanic", "TNFD_code": "C5.0", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Land; Steps: Assess, Prioritise; Pressure: geological hazard; metric: hazard zone classification", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E1-9 (physical risks \u2013 geological hazards)", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "India has 4 seismic zones (II\u2013V); BIS IS 1893. NDMA landslide atlas covers 17 Himalayan and Western Ghat states. GSI (Geological Survey of India) provides hazard data.", "Darukaa_status": "planned", "input_data_required": "seismic hazard maps, DEM, soil type, slope, rainfall data", "open_data_sources": ["NDMA landslide hazard atlas India", "GSI geological maps", "USGS ShakeMap seismic", "NASA SRTM DEM", "ISRO Bhuvan disaster portal"], "access_type": "mixed", "computation_complexity": "medium", "example_use_case": "A hydropower developer in Uttarakhand discloses landslide risk to infrastructure using NDMA/GSI hazard maps in TNFD Assess site-level risk disclosure.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Biodiversity Loss (risk)", "category": "Biodiversity & ecosystems", "sub_category": "biodiversity loss risk", "short_description": "Decline of local ecosystem health impacting ecosystem services like pollination", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-A (Assess): nature-related risk from biodiversity decline; LEAP-P (Prepare): risk management response; Risk disclosure", "TNFD_metric_type": "nature-related risk \u2013 biodiversity transition risk", "TNFD_code": "C5.0", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Land; Steps: Interpret, Prioritise; Pressure: all; metric: composite biodiversity loss risk score", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E4-1 (IRO \u2013 biodiversity transition risk); ESRS 2 (ESRS IRO assessment)", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "Composite risk metric; calibrate with India's Biodiversity Act 2002, NBA data, National Green Tribunal rulings as regulatory risk factors.", "Darukaa_status": "prototype", "input_data_required": "MSA score, threatened species count, protected area proximity, regulatory layer", "open_data_sources": ["IUCN Red List", "GBIF", "WDPA WCMC", "India NBA Biodiversity Management Committees", "MoEFCC EIA notifications"], "access_type": "mixed", "computation_complexity": "medium", "example_use_case": "A financial institution screens its loan portfolio for biodiversity loss risk exposure across Indian operational sites using this composite score for TNFD risk disclosure.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Earthquake", "category": "Climate & physical risk", "sub_category": "geophysical & mass movement risk", "short_description": "Seismic risk with potential structural damage ranging from minor to catastrophic", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-A (Assess): geophysical risk at site; Risk disclosure", "TNFD_metric_type": "physical risk \u2013 seismic / landslide / volcanic", "TNFD_code": "C5.0", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Land; Steps: Assess, Prioritise; Pressure: geological hazard; metric: hazard zone classification", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E1-9 (physical risks \u2013 geological hazards)", "India_relevance": "medium", "India_notes": "India has 4 seismic zones (II\u2013V); BIS IS 1893.