; Pressure: climate change; metric: temperature/precipitation trend", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E1-9 (physical risk assessment \u2013 baseline climate); ESRS E1-4 (transition activities)", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "India Meteorological Department (IMD) provides gridded climate data (1\u00b0 grid, 1901\u2013present) and station data. ERA5-Land freely available for historical analysis. SAFAR network for urban climate.", "Darukaa_status": "available", "input_data_required": "IMD gridded data, ERA5-Land reanalysis, NOAA GHCN station data", "open_data_sources": ["IMD India gridded climate data", "ERA5-Land (Copernicus CDS)", "NASA POWER", "NOAA GHCN", "Open-Meteo Historical API"], "access_type": "open", "computation_complexity": "low", "example_use_case": "A bank screens its agricultural loan portfolio for historical temperature and rainfall trends at district level to quantify climate risk exposure under TCFD/TNFD physical risk assessment.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Future Temperature", "category": "Climate & physical risk", "sub_category": "climate projection (SSP)", "short_description": "Climate temperature projections based on SSP scenarios", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-A (Assess): forward-looking physical climate risk under multiple scenarios; LEAP-P (Prepare): scenario planning; Risk & Opportunity", "TNFD_metric_type": "physical risk \u2013 climate projections (SSP1-2.6, SSP2-4.5, SSP5-8.5)", "TNFD_code": "IFRS S2", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Atmosphere; Steps: Interpret, Prioritise; Pressure: future climate stress; metric: projected temperature/precipitation change", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E1-9 (physical risk \u2013 climate scenarios); ESRS E1-3 (climate scenario analysis); ESRS 2-SBM-3 (scenario analysis)", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "CMIP6 projections downscaled for India available via IMD/IITM CORDEX-SA. India's NDC scenarios align with SSP1-1.9 ambition. DSS NATCOM provides official projections.", "Darukaa_status": "avai