s. GloFAS provides global river discharge forecasts. High relevance for hydropower, water-intensive manufacturing, and coastal cities.", "Darukaa_status": "planned", "input_data_required": "CWC stream gauge data, GloFAS model output, DEM, GRACE", "open_data_sources": ["CWC India river gauge network", "GloFAS (Copernicus EMS)", "HydroSHEDS", "NASA GRACE groundwater", "FAO AQUASTAT India"], "access_type": "mixed", "computation_complexity": "medium", "example_use_case": "A beverage company at a drought-prone river basin in Andhra Pradesh uses CWC discharge data to disclose freshwater availability risk and set water targets under ESRS E3-4 and TNFD Assess.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "PM10", "category": "Air quality & pollution", "sub_category": "particulate matter", "short_description": "PM10 coarse particulate matter concentration over time", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-A (Assess): air pollution as health risk and transition risk; Risk & Impact", "TNFD_metric_type": "impacts \u2013 air quality / health risk", "TNFD_code": "C2.4", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Atmosphere; Steps: Assess; Pressure: air pollution; metric: PM2.5/PM10 \u00b5g/m\u00b3", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E2-4 (air pollutants \u2013 PM2.5/PM10); ESRS E2-3 (material pollution policy); ESRS S1-9 (worker health)", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "India has 14 of world's 20 most polluted cities by PM2.5 (IQAir). CPCB CAAQM network provides real-time PM data. SAFAR network covers 7 major cities. MPCB, SPCB data at state level.", "Darukaa_status": "prototype", "input_data_required": "CPCB/SPCB PM monitors, Sentinel-5P AOD, MERRA-2 PM2.5", "open_data_sources": ["CPCB CAAQM India (real-time)", "OpenAQ India data", "NASA MERRA-2 PM2.5", "Sentinel-5P TROPOMI AOD", "WHO Air Quality database India"], "access_type": "mixed", "computation_complexity": "low", "example_use_case": "A cement plant in Rajasthan uses CPCB CAAQM and Sentinel-5P data to disclose PM2.5 emissions impact on surrounding communities