lution; metric: AOD", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E2-4 (air pollutants \u2013 particulates, aerosols)", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "AOD from MODIS and Sentinel-5P widely used for Indian air quality assessment. IMD SAFAR provides MODIS-based AOD. ISRO has long-term aerosol research over Indian subcontinent.", "Darukaa_status": "prototype", "input_data_required": "MODIS MOD04 AOD, Sentinel-5P UVAI, AERONET station data", "open_data_sources": ["MODIS MOD04_3K AOD", "Sentinel-5P UVAI (Copernicus)", "AERONET India stations", "IMD SAFAR", "NASA MERRA-2 AOD"], "access_type": "open", "computation_complexity": "low", "example_use_case": "A logistics company monitors aerosol optical depth trends near its transport corridors in Delhi using MODIS AOD data to assess air quality risks for driver health under ESRS S1-9 and E2-4.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "UV Index", "category": "Air quality & pollution", "sub_category": "UV & radiation exposure", "short_description": "Ultraviolet radiation index over time", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-A (Assess): UV radiation as environmental health risk; Risk", "TNFD_metric_type": "physical risk \u2013 UV radiation", "TNFD_code": "C5.0", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Atmosphere; Steps: Assess; Pressure: ozone depletion; metric: UV Index", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E1-9 (physical risk \u2013 UV); ESRS S1-9 (worker health \u2013 UV exposure)", "India_relevance": "medium", "India_notes": "UV Index from Sentinel-5P and TROPOMI. Relevant for outdoor workers in high-UV areas of Rajasthan, Gujarat. India Meteorological Department issues UV alerts.", "Darukaa_status": "not_core", "input_data_required": "Sentinel-5P TROPOMI UV, TEMIS UV climatology", "open_data_sources": ["Sentinel-5P TROPOMI UV", "TEMIS UV climatology", "WOUDC UV data", "Open-Meteo UV Index", "NASA TOMS/OMI UV"], "access_type": "open", "computation_complexity": "low", "example_use_case": "A construction company assesses UV exposure risk for outdoor workers at project sites