": "CPCB AQI system (India-specific 6 pollutant composite, scale 0\u2013500) is the standard. India AQI differs from US/EU systems. SAFAR provides city-specific AQI. National Clean Air Programme (NCAP) targets 40% PM reduction by 2026.", "Darukaa_status": "prototype", "input_data_required": "CPCB CAAQM AQI, PM2.5, PM10, NO2, SO2, O3, CO data", "open_data_sources": ["CPCB AQI India (real-time)", "SAFAR India AQI", "OpenAQ India", "IQAir India data", "WAQI World Air Quality Index"], "access_type": "mixed", "computation_complexity": "low", "example_use_case": "A real-estate developer uses India AQI data to disclose environmental quality around residential projects in Delhi-NCR for ESRS E2-4 community exposure indicators and BRSR ESG reporting.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "US Air Quality Index", "category": "Air quality & pollution", "sub_category": "air quality index", "short_description": "US AQI composite air quality index over time", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-A (Assess): composite air quality health risk; Risk & Impact", "TNFD_metric_type": "impacts \u2013 air quality composite index", "TNFD_code": "C2.4", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Atmosphere; Steps: Assess; Pressure: air pollution; metric: AQI score", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E2-4 (air pollutants); ESRS S1-9 (worker/community health \u2013 air quality)", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "CPCB AQI system (India-specific 6 pollutant composite, scale 0\u2013500) is the standard. India AQI differs from US/EU systems. SAFAR provides city-specific AQI. National Clean Air Programme (NCAP) targets 40% PM reduction by 2026.", "Darukaa_status": "prototype", "input_data_required": "CPCB CAAQM AQI, PM2.5, PM10, NO2, SO2, O3, CO data", "open_data_sources": ["CPCB AQI India (real-time)", "SAFAR India AQI", "OpenAQ India", "IQAir India data", "WAQI World Air Quality Index"], "access_type": "mixed", "computation_complexity": "low", "example_use_case": "A real-estate developer uses India AQI data to disclose environmental quality around residential projects in Delhi-NCR for ESRS E2-4 community exposure indicators and BRSR ESG reporting.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Landslides (KPI)", "category": "Climate & physical risk", "sub_category": "geophysical & mass movement risk", "short_description": "Landslide and erosion risk assessment based on past events", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-A (Assess): geophysical risk at site; Risk disclosure", "TNFD_metric_type": "physical risk \u2013 seismic / landslide / volcanic", "TNFD_code": "C5.0", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Land; Steps: Assess, Prioritise; Pressure: geological hazard; metric: hazard zone classification", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E1-9 (physical risks \u2013 geological hazards)", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "India has 4 seismic zones (II\u2013V); BIS IS 1893. NDMA landslide atlas covers 17 Himalayan and Western Ghat states. GSI (Geological Survey of India) provides hazard data.", "Darukaa_status": "planned", "input_data_required": "seismic hazard maps, DEM, soil type, slope, rainfall data", "open_data_sources": ["NDMA landslide hazard atlas India", "GSI geological maps", "USGS ShakeMap seismic", "NASA SRTM DEM", "ISRO Bhuvan disaster portal"], "access_type": "mixed", "computation_complexity": "medium", "example_use_case": "A hydropower developer in Uttarakhand discloses landslide risk to infrastructure using NDMA/GSI hazard maps in TNFD Assess site-level risk disclosure.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Distances", "category": "Socio-environmental & exposure", "sub_category": "proximity & accessibility", "short_description": "Distances from the site to geographical features and urban centres", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-L (Locate): geographic context for site proximity to ecosystems and communities; spatial framing", "TNFD_metric_type": "exposure index \u2013 proximity to features", "TNFD_code": "No Annex 1/2 code \u2014 relates to TNFD Strategy D (priority locations) and stakeholder engagement guidance", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Land; Steps: Assess; Pressure: location-specific context; metric: distance (km)", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E4-1 (site location relative to sensitive areas); ESRS S3-3 (community proximity)", "India_relevance": "medium", "India_notes": "Useful baseline metric; combine with India-specific layers: distance to National Highways (NHAI), proximity to IBA/Ramsar/Biosphere Reserves.", "Darukaa_status": "not_core", "input_data_required": "OSM road/river networks, protected area polygons, population centres", "open_data_sources": ["OpenStreetMap (OSM)", "WCMC WDPA India", "NHAI road network India", "ISRO Bhuvan watershed layers", "Natural Earth datasets"], "access_type": "open", "computation_complexity": "low", "example_use_case": "A project developer calculates distances from its industrial site to the nearest Ramsar wetland and National Highway for TNFD Locate context and ESRS E4-1 biodiversity policy site screening.", "additional_comments": null}, {"original_name": "Protected Areas Index", "category": "Compliance & proximity to protected/sensitive areas", "sub_category": "protected area proximity", "short_description": "KPI based on proximity and coverage of protected areas around the site", "TNFD_link": "LEAP-L (Locate): mandatory step to identify operations in/near protected areas; Compliance & Risk", "TNFD_metric_type": "compliance \u2013 protected area proximity", "TNFD_code": "C5.0 | C1.1", "SBTN_link": "Realm: Land/Freshwater/Ocean; Steps: Assess, Interpret; Pressure: all; metric: % operations in/near protected areas", "CSRD_ESRS_link": "ESRS E4-1 (biodiversity-sensitive areas \u2013 protected area proximity); ESRS E4-2 (policy for sensitive areas)", "India_relevance": "high", "India_notes": "India has 900+ Protected Areas (National Parks, Sanctuaries, Conservation Reserves) under WPA 1972, plus Eco-Sensitive Zones (ESZ) under EPA. MoEFCC and ENVIS PA data. SEAC/SEIAA require PA proximity in EIA.", "Darukaa_status": "available", "input_da